Automatic Data Processing Inc Raises Low End Of Prior FY 2013 Guidance To A Range In Line With Analysts' Estimates
Friday, 3 May 2013 07:30am EDT
Automatic Data Processing Inc announced that for fiscal 2013, it expects revenue of 6%-7% growth compared with prior forecast of 5%-7% growth. The Company expects diluted earnings per share (EPS) from continuing operations of 6%- 7% growth compared to $2.72 in fiscal 2012, which excludes the gain recorded in the second quarter of fiscal 2012. Prior forecast was for 5%-7% growth. The Company reported revenue of $10.66 billion in fiscal 2012. According to I/B/E/S Estimates, analysts on an average are expecting the Company to report revenue of $11.30 billion and EPS of $2.91 for fiscal 2013.Â 
